klinite, willemite, and calcite</a><span>Specimen showing bright fluorescen=
t colour resulting from ultraviolet irradiation of calcite (calcium carbona=
te; red fluorescence) with grains of franklinite (a zinc, manganese, and ir=
on oxide; black coloration), which is nonfluorescent. Veins and grains of w=
illemite (a zinc silicate; green fluorescence) also appear.</span><button c=
